Orjan Johansen wrote:
>
>On Sat, 18 Apr 1998, Ed Murphy wrote:
>
>> I hereby Call for Judgement on the following statement:
>> 
>>      If a Player with nonzero Score deregisters and later re-registers,
>>      eir Score is the same as it was when e deregistered.
>
>Most peculiar.
>
>By Rule 1775, only Players can have a Score, and all Players do.
>By Rule 1782, the Score of a Player cannot change except by the proper
>procedure.
>
>The former has precedence.

I don't quite see the peculiarity. I would interpret these provisions
taken together to imply that a Player does not have a Score while e
is deregistered, but that e resumes with eir old Score upon reregistering.
(R1432 is relevant here.)

